# Implementation Plan - Phase 2: User Authentication & Access Control

This plan guides the implementation of user registration, login, JWT authentication middleware, Axios interceptors, Socket.IO authentication handshake, private routing, and the global auth state context.

## Proposed Package Additions (Frontend)
We will install the following packages in `frontend/`:
- `axios` (For making promise-based HTTP requests to the backend)
- `react-router-dom` (For client-side routing and protected routes)

---

## Proposed Changes

### Backend Components

#### [NEW] [User.js](file:///e:/Vishal%20Folder/codec%20intern/Collaborative%20Document%20Editor/backend/models/User.js)
Define a Mongoose schema for User profiles containing `name`, `email`, `password` (hashed), and `createdAt`.

#### [NEW] [authController.js](file:///e:/Vishal%20Folder/codec%20intern/Collaborative%20Document%20Editor/backend/controllers/authController.js)
Provide route handlers for registering new accounts (validating inputs, hashing passwords with bcrypt, saving, and issuing a JWT token) and logging in existing users (verifying email, comparing bcrypt hashes, and returning a JWT token).

#### [NEW] [authMiddleware.js](file:///e:/Vishal%20Folder/codec%20intern/Collaborative%20Document%20Editor/backend/middleware/authMiddleware.js)
An Express middleware that checks the HTTP request's `Authorization: Bearer <token>` header, decodes the token, and attaches the user's ID to `req.user`.

#### [NEW] [authRoutes.js](file:///e:/Vishal%20Folder/codec%20intern/Collaborative%20Document%20Editor/backend/routes/authRoutes.js)
Exposes endpoint paths `/api/auth/register` and `/api/auth/login` to mapping triggers.

#### [MODIFY] [server.js](file:///e:/Vishal%20Folder/codec%20intern/Collaborative%20Document%20Editor/backend/server.js)
- Register user authentication HTTP routes.
- Create custom Socket.IO connection middleware to parse and verify the JWT signature sent during the handshake from the client side, blocking unauthorized WebSockets.

