### Frontend Components

#### [NEW] [api.js](file:///e:/Vishal%20Folder/codec%20intern/Collaborative%20Document%20Editor/frontend/src/services/api.js)
Instantiates an Axios client pointing to our backend API. Integrates an interceptor that automatically reads the user token from `localStorage` and appends it to the `Authorization` header on every request.

#### [NEW] [AuthContext.jsx](file:///e:/Vishal%20Folder/codec%20intern/Collaborative%20Document%20Editor/frontend/src/context/AuthContext.jsx)
Implements a React context wrapper that coordinates global user state, stores login tokens, loads active credentials from local cache, and manages the user login/logout functions.

#### [NEW] [PrivateRoute.jsx](file:///e:/Vishal%20Folder/codec%20intern/Collaborative%20Document%20Editor/frontend/src/components/PrivateRoute.jsx)
A wrapper component that inspects the current authenticated user state; redirects to `/login` if unauthenticated, otherwise renders the child page views.

#### [NEW] [Navbar.jsx](file:///e:/Vishal%20Folder/codec%20intern/Collaborative%20Document%20Editor/frontend/src/components/Navbar.jsx)
A navigation header that displays the user's name and email if logged in, plus a logout action button.

#### [NEW] [Register.jsx](file:///e:/Vishal%20Folder/codec%20intern/Collaborative%20Document%20Editor/frontend/src/pages/Register.jsx)
An interactive signup layout with field validations that submits registration details to the API.

#### [NEW] [Login.jsx](file:///e:/Vishal%20Folder/codec%20intern/Collaborative%20Document%20Editor/frontend/src/pages/Login.jsx)
A login form layout that submits email and password parameters and saves the returned JWT.

#### [NEW] [Dashboard.jsx](file:///e:/Vishal%20Folder/codec%20intern/Collaborative%20Document%20Editor/frontend/src/pages/Dashboard.jsx)
A placeholder dashboard page for logged-in users to display when authentication is validated.

#### [MODIFY] [App.jsx](file:///e:/Vishal%20Folder/codec%20intern/Collaborative%20Document%20Editor/frontend/src/App.jsx)
Configures client routing (`/`, `/login`, `/register`, `/dashboard`) using React Router, wraps components with `AuthProvider`, and applies `PrivateRoute` wrappers to dashboard components.

